WEBVTT

00:13.638 --> 00:17.058
[Film reel buzzing]

00:33.241 --> 00:38.413
[***]

00:50.342 --> 00:54.262
[***]

00:54.304 --> 00:56.348
Max: The Sisters
Of The Holy Tears Convent

00:56.389 --> 00:58.516
had taken in Archie's mother
when she was orphaned

00:58.558 --> 01:01.728
and Archie always felt
a great affinity for them.

01:01.770 --> 01:03.730
So after the Loswaki massacre,

01:03.772 --> 01:06.232
he thought it would be
an interesting and safe subject

01:06.274 --> 01:07.442
for Alba to tackle.

01:07.484 --> 01:09.444
- The nuns were a hoot.

01:09.486 --> 01:11.237
For every natural event,

01:11.279 --> 01:13.365
there was a supernatural
interpretation.

01:13.406 --> 01:15.700
If a butterfly
flew in the window,

01:15.742 --> 01:20.205
they'd declare
"A letter will arrive today."

01:20.246 --> 01:22.374
If milk boiled over
on the stove,

01:22.415 --> 01:24.292
they'd say, "We must be careful,

01:24.334 --> 01:27.170
someone
in the sisterhood is sick."

01:27.212 --> 01:31.758
They all played the lottery
a lot, but never won.

01:31.800 --> 01:34.594
-And they insisted on traveling
without anyone else,

01:34.636 --> 01:36.554
always, didn't they?

01:36.596 --> 01:40.225
- Yes, they made me drive my car
behind their bus.

01:40.266 --> 01:42.644
- The, uh, the weather
for the day of the field trip

01:42.686 --> 01:45.730
called for a cloudless,
sunny day.

01:49.818 --> 01:51.361
- Yes.

01:51.403 --> 01:52.654
[Thunder roars]

01:54.322 --> 01:58.243
Max: After the accident,
Alba lost track of time.

01:58.284 --> 02:00.203
She felt hollow.

02:00.245 --> 02:01.371
She grew tired.

02:01.413 --> 02:03.790
She would gaze
at the birds in the ocean

02:03.832 --> 02:06.668
and felt deeply moved by
the life humming inside them.

02:10.213 --> 02:12.215
Alba: I dropped my guard.

02:12.257 --> 02:14.634
I knew there were
magical moments to cling to

02:14.676 --> 02:17.387
and I felt alert
towards the things around me,

02:17.429 --> 02:19.305
especially the birds.

02:19.347 --> 02:22.600
But it's as if someone
got inside my body at night,

02:22.642 --> 02:24.227
not sexually, but like,

02:24.269 --> 02:27.230
a scientist got in there
and rewired all my parts

02:27.272 --> 02:29.774
but didn't put them
back in the right place.

02:32.277 --> 02:33.653
[Glass clatters]

02:33.695 --> 02:35.488
Maybe less of a scientist

02:35.530 --> 02:38.283
and more
of a Mexican electrician,

02:38.324 --> 02:39.784
someone accustomed
to improvising.

02:41.494 --> 02:44.330
And when I looked in the mirror

02:44.372 --> 02:46.374
I could see
the difference right away.

02:47.709 --> 02:50.670
After three days,
the evidence was undeniable.

02:52.547 --> 02:54.674
I had started losing luminosity.

02:58.345 --> 03:01.598
I would lie out in the sun
trying to soak in nature,

03:01.639 --> 03:03.516
but I was fading fast.

03:06.895 --> 03:08.730
I lost track of time.

03:10.648 --> 03:12.400
I lost track of everything.

03:14.486 --> 03:15.695
[Water splashing]

03:15.737 --> 03:18.406
I felt like I was melting.

03:26.748 --> 03:29.668
[***]

03:29.709 --> 03:32.420
[Water blooping]

03:39.386 --> 03:42.430
Being a trained documentarian,
I could think of no other option

03:42.472 --> 03:44.474
than to photograph
my deterioration

03:44.516 --> 03:45.809
before it was too late.

03:48.853 --> 03:50.814
Every day,
I photographed my face,

03:50.855 --> 03:53.400
paying close
attention to my eyes.

03:53.441 --> 03:56.569
I was a bit astonished
I could bear the spectacle.

03:56.611 --> 04:00.532
I felt like
a corpse being eaten by worms.

04:00.573 --> 04:02.742
What was I looking
for in these photos?

04:02.784 --> 04:04.411
I don't know.

04:04.452 --> 04:05.995
I felt there
was something there,

04:06.037 --> 04:08.581
but I couldn't tell you what.

04:08.623 --> 04:11.084
I can't remember a single
conversation with my husband

04:11.126 --> 04:12.377
during those two months.

04:12.419 --> 04:16.589
All I remember is
one time saying out loud...

04:16.631 --> 04:18.383
I think we're floundering.

04:22.804 --> 04:24.597
Max: 63 days after she began

04:24.639 --> 04:26.307
her reflective
self-portrait series,

04:26.349 --> 04:27.934
her husband
started having an affair

04:27.976 --> 04:29.686
with a local restaurant hostess.

04:36.234 --> 04:43.742
[***]

04:43.783 --> 04:45.410
[***]

04:47.620 --> 04:49.998
[Birds chirping]

04:50.040 --> 04:53.710
[***]

05:10.685 --> 05:11.770
- Hi.

05:14.689 --> 05:16.983
- Hi.

05:17.025 --> 05:19.486
- Can I ask you something?

05:19.527 --> 05:22.530
- My plate is full,
but I can spare a minute.

05:22.572 --> 05:23.907
- What are you doing?

05:23.948 --> 05:26.076
- What does it look like?

05:26.117 --> 05:29.579
- Don't make me feel stupider
than I already do.

05:30.205 --> 05:32.248
- There is a joke
to be made here,

05:32.290 --> 05:34.125
but I can't remember jokes.

05:35.543 --> 05:37.087
Oh, wait, there's one I like.

05:37.128 --> 05:39.506
A waiter is
serving a plate of beans

05:39.547 --> 05:41.466
and drops it
on the customer's lap,

05:41.508 --> 05:43.885
so he says, "Oh, oh,
I spilled the beans."

05:47.931 --> 05:51.935
I'm Batista,
but everybody calls me Batty.

05:51.976 --> 05:53.019
Who are you?

05:53.061 --> 05:54.562
- Alba.

05:54.604 --> 05:57.607
- Oh, dear.
You are Archie's ex.

05:57.649 --> 06:00.860
- Is... is that what he said?

06:00.902 --> 06:03.738
- He told me about you.

06:03.780 --> 06:07.909
- I am so sorry
about those nuns in the bus.

06:07.951 --> 06:11.037
Are you feeling better
after your breakdown?

06:11.079 --> 06:14.499
I'm only trying to get a tan,
to answer your initial question.

06:14.541 --> 06:16.960
I did not mean to upset you.

06:17.002 --> 06:17.961
- You didn't.

06:18.003 --> 06:21.131
- Well, you're upset.

06:21.172 --> 06:24.092
- Here we go
round the prickly pear.

06:24.134 --> 06:25.552
- Excuse me?

06:33.560 --> 06:35.770
- This is my house, yes?

06:37.022 --> 06:39.858
-  Archie said you and he
had worked everything out,

06:39.899 --> 06:42.694
but if there's some stuff
you need to pick up

06:42.736 --> 06:44.904
or if you want to take a look
around the place one last time,

06:44.946 --> 06:46.656
by all means.

06:46.698 --> 06:48.658
- To be honest,
right this minute,

06:48.700 --> 06:51.661
I'm not thinking
about either of those things.

06:51.703 --> 06:53.788
- I've never been
in this situation before.

06:53.830 --> 06:55.999
I'm trying to put myself
in your shoes.

06:56.041 --> 06:57.834
- Oh.
[chuckles]

06:57.876 --> 07:00.837
Well, don't worry
if it doesn't work out.

07:00.879 --> 07:02.589
- Let me get you some water.

07:02.630 --> 07:03.256
Inocencia!

07:07.177 --> 07:09.846
- Ms. Alba.

07:09.888 --> 07:11.556
- You know this person?

07:14.726 --> 07:16.644
- We just met.

07:16.686 --> 07:17.896
- Well, we met last week

07:17.937 --> 07:19.939
when Archie
brought me over to meet you.

07:21.816 --> 07:24.652
You seem a little pale.
Are you feeling sick?

07:24.694 --> 07:27.697
- At the moment, no.
But it doesn't look good.

07:27.739 --> 07:29.991
- Inocencia, water.
Quickly, please.

07:34.871 --> 07:37.832
- Terrible accent.

07:37.874 --> 07:39.793
- We can both agree
that your pride is wounded

07:39.834 --> 07:41.711
and that might be clouding
your outlook on things,

07:41.753 --> 07:43.922
so accept
the water and get going.

07:50.845 --> 07:51.888
- Thank you.

08:04.776 --> 08:05.819
[Water splashes]

08:10.115 --> 08:11.991
- You missed most of my face.

08:12.033 --> 08:14.077
Plus, we're in a beach house.

08:14.119 --> 08:16.830
I am not wearing any clothes.

08:16.871 --> 08:18.957
So none of this behavior
is doing anything

08:18.998 --> 08:23.086
except making you seem sadder...

08:23.128 --> 08:24.921
and blinder.

08:24.963 --> 08:27.757
I am not the reason Archie
fell out of love with you.

08:27.799 --> 08:29.259
I'm the shoulder he cries on.

08:29.300 --> 08:33.054
Yes, I give him a hard-on,
but mostly I listen to him,

08:33.096 --> 08:35.974
and in return, he pampers me
and he takes care of me.

08:36.891 --> 08:39.185
- The eyes are not here.

08:39.227 --> 08:41.980
There are no eyes here.

08:42.022 --> 08:44.733
In this valley of dying stars.

08:44.774 --> 08:47.193
In this hollow valley.

08:47.235 --> 08:49.988
This broken jaw
of our lost kingdoms.

08:50.030 --> 08:51.656
[Chuckles]

08:53.950 --> 08:56.995
- I don't know that song,
I'm sorry.

08:57.037 --> 08:59.122
- I don't want your charity
and understanding.

08:59.164 --> 09:01.666
[Birds chirping]

09:03.501 --> 09:07.005
[***]

09:08.882 --> 09:10.300
Alba: What is a marriage anyway?

09:10.342 --> 09:13.887
[***]

09:18.808 --> 09:20.143
I moved into
a small apartment

09:20.185 --> 09:21.978
in a sorry little town

09:22.020 --> 09:26.191
not far,
but a million miles away.

09:26.232 --> 09:29.277
I met a young trumpet player.

09:29.319 --> 09:31.279
He was almost never home.
It was perfect.

09:31.321 --> 09:36.034
[***]

09:36.076 --> 09:38.244
We fucked.
We fought.

09:38.286 --> 09:39.996
[Indistinct argument]

09:40.038 --> 09:42.791
One morning
I found his heroin stash.

09:42.832 --> 09:47.087
That sounds like the beginning
of a strange time and it was.

09:47.128 --> 09:49.756
What if you never thought
you were the kind of person

09:49.798 --> 09:53.051
who has an addictive personality
and then found out you were?

09:53.093 --> 09:56.096
[***]

09:59.849 --> 10:03.103
[***]

10:06.981 --> 10:08.441
[Bell tinkling]

10:08.483 --> 10:11.027
Eventually I went to a shaman
in the jungle to clean up.

10:11.069 --> 10:14.030
He gave me better drugs.
Natural ones.

10:14.072 --> 10:15.865
The first flower, he called it.

10:17.992 --> 10:21.079
[bells tinkling]

10:24.124 --> 10:25.917
I had a vision.

10:25.959 --> 10:27.961
Not one.
Many.

10:28.003 --> 10:30.213
But basically one
in many different variations.

10:30.255 --> 10:33.174
[***]

10:35.802 --> 10:38.013
[***]

10:38.054 --> 10:42.100
[Electricity crackles]

10:42.142 --> 10:46.062
[***]

10:55.280 --> 10:57.907
[Water gurgling]

11:00.994 --> 11:03.788
[***]

11:06.082 --> 11:07.375
When I returned to my senses,

11:07.417 --> 11:10.086
I remembered many things
I never knew before.

11:10.128 --> 11:12.255
Number one:
my grandmother was a psychic.

11:12.297 --> 11:14.090
She had the gift.

11:14.132 --> 11:16.885
And when I was a child,
one night she came into my room

11:16.926 --> 11:18.428
and whispered
something in my ear.

11:18.470 --> 11:20.347
Blue smoke came out of her mouth

11:20.388 --> 11:22.349
and swirled
in front of my eyes...

11:22.390 --> 11:27.020
I can still remember it.
The smoke spelled out a word.

11:27.062 --> 11:30.273
The word was "death."

11:30.315 --> 11:32.233
I didn't know what it meant

11:32.275 --> 11:34.110
but I knew
it meant something important.

11:39.074 --> 11:40.909
[Door opens]

11:40.950 --> 11:42.952
- Miss Alba!
[Chuckles]

11:42.994 --> 11:47.165
- [Sighs]
I have these dreams, Inocencia.

11:47.207 --> 11:49.209
Horrible things.
You wouldn't believe it.

11:50.877 --> 11:52.962
How are things here?

11:53.004 --> 11:55.256
- It's not the same without you.

11:55.298 --> 11:56.216
- Does he seem happy?

12:00.011 --> 12:02.347
- I don't know.
- Does she seem happy?

12:04.265 --> 12:06.101
- I don't know.

12:06.142 --> 12:08.019
- What do they do?

12:08.061 --> 12:10.897
- He's away on business
more than usual.

12:10.939 --> 12:13.316
She gets drunk
and dances by herself,

12:13.358 --> 12:15.485
watches Kung Fu movies,
and cries.

12:15.527 --> 12:17.487
- How does she treat you?

12:17.529 --> 12:19.280
- Uh, she doesn't like me.

12:19.322 --> 12:21.491
She accuses me
of stealing her things.

12:21.533 --> 12:23.201
- Inocencia, that's terrible.

12:23.243 --> 12:26.162
- Nothing I can't handle.
But tell me about you.

12:26.204 --> 12:28.998
You have lost weight,
but not in a good way.

12:29.040 --> 12:31.918
- [Chuckles] I can always count
on you to tell me the truth.

12:31.960 --> 12:34.087
- Are you on
a military diet

12:34.129 --> 12:35.964
or have you become a junkie?

12:36.006 --> 12:38.341
- I went through a phase,
but I'm on the other side.

12:38.383 --> 12:40.010
- God knows you've been
through a lot

12:40.051 --> 12:41.094
to develop many addictions.

12:41.136 --> 12:42.595
Drugs are not
for the weak of heart.

12:42.637 --> 12:45.890
You wake up one morning
and your hair is on fire.

12:45.932 --> 12:47.225
Are you still
taking photographs?

12:47.267 --> 12:49.978
- No, no. Thankfully, no.
How is your family?

12:50.020 --> 12:51.146
- Good.
- Yeah?

12:51.187 --> 12:52.480
- My nephew Raimundo.
- Raimundo?

12:52.522 --> 12:54.482
- Yeah, my sister's son.
[chuckles]

12:54.524 --> 12:57.444
He's a little wild,
but so smart.

12:57.485 --> 12:59.988
He's grown into
a proper young man.

13:00.030 --> 13:02.991
He's thinking about college.
[laughs] Can you imagine?

13:03.033 --> 13:06.286
The first in the family.
Where did we go wrong?

13:08.371 --> 13:10.498
- Inocencia.
- Yes?

13:10.540 --> 13:12.959
- Is there anything
strange going on here?

13:14.294 --> 13:16.212
- Well, with Archibaldo,

13:16.254 --> 13:20.091
everything is a little strange,
you know this.

13:20.133 --> 13:22.469
- I'm afraid...

13:22.510 --> 13:26.514
No, I'm convinced
she's in terrible danger.

13:26.556 --> 13:27.932
How?

13:29.309 --> 13:30.977
I'm convinced he will kill her.

13:34.189 --> 13:35.315
Let me show you something.

13:38.109 --> 13:42.405
[Footsteps]

13:42.447 --> 13:45.950
[Clattering]

13:49.996 --> 13:51.081
[Bottle thuds]

13:51.122 --> 13:52.123
[Chair slides]

13:52.165 --> 13:53.583
- What is it?

13:53.625 --> 13:55.585
- I took a pinch to my village.

13:55.627 --> 13:58.380
I showed it to my uncle Ulises,
he's a pharmacist.

13:58.421 --> 14:01.591
He knows everything
about chemicals and poisons.

14:01.633 --> 14:04.260
He told me this comes
from a Japanese fish

14:04.302 --> 14:06.096
that rich people
pay a lot of money

14:06.137 --> 14:07.305
to eat in restaurants,

14:07.347 --> 14:10.183
but if it goes
into your bloodstream

14:10.225 --> 14:12.435
a certain way,

14:12.477 --> 14:14.562
it paralyzes you.

14:14.604 --> 14:16.564
- You think he's poisoning her?

14:16.606 --> 14:19.150
- I think she is poisoning him.

14:21.236 --> 14:23.154
Alba: What?
Inosencia: Hmm.

14:23.196 --> 14:25.615
I saw it two weeks ago,
with my very own eyes.

14:25.657 --> 14:28.159
Alba: Are you sure?
Inosencia: I saw her.

14:28.201 --> 14:31.329
[Spoon clinking]

14:31.371 --> 14:32.539
[Clattering]

14:34.416 --> 14:36.584
- But it's so clear
in my dreams.

14:36.626 --> 14:38.003
She's in danger.

14:38.044 --> 14:41.464
- Maybe your dream
is an inverse prediction.

14:41.506 --> 14:43.341
It happens.

14:43.383 --> 14:47.512
[Clock ticking]

14:50.181 --> 14:52.392
Alba: A week later, I returned.

14:52.434 --> 14:55.270
[***]

14:58.565 --> 15:04.070
[Humming]

15:04.112 --> 15:07.574
[Singing in Spanish]

15:07.615 --> 15:11.536
[***]

15:30.347 --> 15:34.184
[***]

15:42.150 --> 15:44.152
[Liquid pouring]

15:44.194 --> 15:46.988
[***]

15:51.117 --> 15:55.997
[Indistinct TV conversation]

16:02.170 --> 16:03.630
[Sighs]

16:03.672 --> 16:05.548
[Sobs]

16:09.594 --> 16:12.597
- Ah, you scared me.
Batty: Did I?

16:12.639 --> 16:14.182
Tell me about your visitor.

16:16.184 --> 16:17.477
- What visitor?

16:17.519 --> 16:19.229
- Let me explain to you
something about me

16:19.270 --> 16:21.231
that you may not
have figured out.

16:21.272 --> 16:23.274
I hate thieves and I hate liars.

16:23.316 --> 16:25.151
- Me, too.

16:25.193 --> 16:27.487
You know, that reminds me
of what Doña Leticia

16:27.529 --> 16:29.531
- was telling to her daughter...
- You don't understand.

16:31.366 --> 16:32.492
- What?

16:32.534 --> 16:34.452
- It must be a drag,
living on scraps,

16:34.494 --> 16:36.496
on whatever
the hot shots let fall.

16:36.538 --> 16:39.082
Spend your entire
existence watching others

16:39.124 --> 16:40.291
get what they want,

16:40.333 --> 16:42.460
while you're stuck here
watching TV.

16:43.378 --> 16:45.505
- Have I done something
to upset you?

16:45.547 --> 16:46.840
- As I was saying,

16:46.881 --> 16:48.258
living in self-respecting
poverty is insulting,

16:48.299 --> 16:49.592
no matter how you slice it.

16:49.634 --> 16:51.511
But see,
I think life must be lived

16:51.553 --> 16:53.388
according to your own terms.

16:53.430 --> 16:56.558
Otherwise, it is my belief,
it's not worth living at all.

16:57.600 --> 16:59.060
What are you drinking?

17:02.397 --> 17:04.357
- Tea.

17:04.399 --> 17:06.693
- May I have a sip?

17:06.735 --> 17:09.362
- You won't like it,
it's gone cold.

17:09.404 --> 17:11.239
But I can make you a new one.

17:11.281 --> 17:13.324
- Let's get realistic,
Inocencia.

17:13.366 --> 17:14.659
-Mm-hm.

17:14.701 --> 17:16.327
- I know you don't like me
and I have a few reasons

17:16.369 --> 17:17.829
not to trust
you a hundred percent.

17:17.871 --> 17:19.372
And you've worked
for Archie since forever,

17:19.414 --> 17:21.458
but I think it's time
for you to move on.

17:21.499 --> 17:23.585
- Is this some kind of game?
- Yes.

17:23.626 --> 17:26.212
It's called
"stop lying to my face."

17:26.254 --> 17:28.131
I know Alba was here
visiting you today.

17:28.173 --> 17:29.341
- No, not today.

17:29.382 --> 17:31.176
- Oh, not today, but other days?

17:31.217 --> 17:33.219
How often does she swing by?

17:33.261 --> 17:35.722
- Well, she came one day.

17:35.764 --> 17:37.599
- But not today.
- No.

17:37.640 --> 17:40.101
- You swear to God.

17:40.143 --> 17:43.188
- I don't take
the Lord's name in vain. No.

17:43.229 --> 17:47.317
- So I'm just being paranoid,
is that it?

17:47.359 --> 17:48.693
- I didn't say that,

17:48.735 --> 17:51.571
but, um, you've been acting
a little nervous lately.

17:51.613 --> 17:55.325
You know, like what you said
about the coconuts this morning.

17:55.367 --> 17:57.744
- Oh, please.
I said I was wondering

17:57.786 --> 17:59.454
if other people
were also paranoid

17:59.496 --> 18:01.164
about coconuts
falling on their heads.

18:01.206 --> 18:02.415
This is something
completely different,

18:02.457 --> 18:03.583
and you know that!

18:03.625 --> 18:05.126
- If you say so.

18:10.674 --> 18:12.676
- I want you
to pack your bags and go.

18:12.717 --> 18:14.761
- [Nervous chuckle]
I'm sorry. You can't just...

18:14.803 --> 18:17.305
- Are you telling me
what I can and cannot do with

18:17.347 --> 18:18.473
my own staff?

18:20.684 --> 18:22.477
- No.

18:22.519 --> 18:24.354
- My staff who steals
my husband's gold watches

18:24.396 --> 18:27.148
and rings and my jewelry
when she thinks I'm not looking?

18:29.317 --> 18:32.362
- I have never stolen anything
in my entire life.

18:34.447 --> 18:36.533
- Goodbye, Inocencia.

18:36.574 --> 18:37.575
- Please.

18:39.703 --> 18:41.329
Don't do this, please.

18:41.371 --> 18:42.455
- Oh, oh, okay.

18:42.497 --> 18:44.374
Are you gonna cry like a baby?

18:44.416 --> 18:45.917
You are fired.

18:47.377 --> 18:50.296
Alba: Two weeks later,
he was dead.

18:53.008 --> 18:55.260
MILLIONAIRE
ARCHIBALDO DE LA COLMENA

18:55.301 --> 18:56.219
HAD HIS LAST DRINK

18:58.388 --> 19:02.434
THE SAD WIDOW

