19:16.656 --> 19:22.454
[***]

19:49.814 --> 19:51.399
[Fridge door clicks open]

19:57.405 --> 19:58.615
[Fridge door closes]

20:01.576 --> 20:03.244
[Chair scrapes]

20:12.420 --> 20:13.588
[Bottle thuds]

20:15.840 --> 20:22.514
[***]

20:54.671 --> 20:57.549
[Coughs]

20:57.590 --> 20:58.675
[Laughs]

20:58.717 --> 21:02.804
[***]

21:37.380 --> 21:38.673
[Exhales]

21:48.600 --> 21:52.354
[***]

21:58.401 --> 22:01.571
[Birds chirping]

22:04.032 --> 22:07.577
[Thunder roars]

22:07.619 --> 22:11.581
[Rain falling]

22:11.623 --> 22:15.585
[Wind blowing]

22:15.627 --> 22:19.422
[Thunder rumbling]

22:22.550 --> 22:23.760
[Doorbell rings]

22:34.896 --> 22:36.606
[Door opens]

22:36.648 --> 22:38.400
- Alba.

22:38.441 --> 22:39.693
- I heard about your loss.

22:41.528 --> 22:43.405
- Can you please not...?

22:46.658 --> 22:47.951
- When you make a documentary,

22:47.992 --> 22:50.578
the main question is
where to put the camera.

22:50.620 --> 22:51.871
Choose correctly,

22:51.913 --> 22:53.748
the subject will reveal
itself organically

22:53.790 --> 22:56.876
and your job is
to stay out of the way.

22:56.918 --> 22:58.795
But no matter what you choose,

22:58.837 --> 23:02.424
there is no overestimating
good luck.

23:02.465 --> 23:04.801
- I am sorry your brain is mush.
I truly am.

23:04.843 --> 23:06.511
You should get
professional help.

23:06.553 --> 23:09.639
But I'm grieving,
this is not a good time.

23:09.681 --> 23:12.892
- I know.
I'm sorry.

23:12.934 --> 23:14.060
Here.

23:14.102 --> 23:15.895
- What is it?

23:15.937 --> 23:19.816
- I know you have very strong
personal feelings about me,

23:19.858 --> 23:22.777
but I want to offer you
my deepest condolences.

23:22.819 --> 23:25.572
- Will you stop it
with the mud already?

23:25.613 --> 23:26.865
What is this?

23:26.906 --> 23:28.033
- It's a movie.

23:28.074 --> 23:30.744
A documentary filmed
from two angles.

23:30.785 --> 23:32.537
One right here,
where it sees you

23:32.579 --> 23:34.956
poisoning Archie's Negroni
three different times

23:34.998 --> 23:37.042
until you got the amount
just right, but then...

23:37.083 --> 23:40.795
And this is where the stroke
of luck comes in.

23:40.837 --> 23:43.089
Right there on the edge
of the gazebo,

23:43.131 --> 23:46.926
looking at the pool,
exactly where he collapses

23:46.968 --> 23:49.012
once the poison surges
through his veins

23:49.054 --> 23:50.680
into his heart.

23:50.722 --> 23:52.098
It remains on this fixed-line,

23:52.140 --> 23:54.642
exactly where you dragged him
to the wheelbarrow

23:54.684 --> 23:56.686
and wheeled him
down to the shore,

23:56.728 --> 23:59.064
where you dumped him.
[Chuckles]

23:59.105 --> 24:02.484
It's uncanny,
when you think of the odds.

24:02.525 --> 24:04.611
But it's all there.

24:04.652 --> 24:08.073
It shows how much effort
it took you to strip him naked.

24:08.114 --> 24:11.117
Then without a doubt,
the most surprising moment

24:11.159 --> 24:13.119
was when you're about
to position him face down

24:13.161 --> 24:14.621
so he'll drown

24:14.662 --> 24:15.872
and you notice his erection

24:15.914 --> 24:18.917
and you can't resist
kissing it goodbye

24:18.958 --> 24:22.796
with such vigorous tenderness.

24:22.837 --> 24:25.799
In that unguarded moment,
I understood you.

24:28.134 --> 24:30.011
Love is rare
because it rarely happens

24:30.053 --> 24:32.597
but some part of you,

24:32.639 --> 24:37.060
the deepest animal
part of you, loved him.

24:37.102 --> 24:39.020
He came and went
in his final moment.

24:40.689 --> 24:42.816
- What...?

24:42.857 --> 24:45.694
What? What do you want?

24:45.735 --> 24:49.531
[Rain falling]

24:54.160 --> 24:55.870
[Chair scraping]

25:02.085 --> 25:03.712
- I want you to see the movie.

25:05.130 --> 25:07.090
There's another copy
in my lawyer's office,

25:07.132 --> 25:09.217
of course, with instructions,

25:09.259 --> 25:12.262
should I suddenly disappear.

25:12.303 --> 25:14.222
I imagine
the Mexican Justice System

25:14.264 --> 25:16.224
will throw every law
and every book

25:16.266 --> 25:17.976
they ever read at you.

25:18.018 --> 25:20.103
Patriarchal societies
do not take kindly

25:20.145 --> 25:22.188
to national treasure
macho philanthropists

25:22.230 --> 25:23.815
being murdered by their wives.

25:23.857 --> 25:27.235
Especially foreigners
like you and me.

25:27.277 --> 25:29.112
I would guess the sentence
they agree upon

25:29.154 --> 25:31.740
will reach into
the multiple lifetimes,

25:31.781 --> 25:33.783
piled on top of one another
and served consecutively

25:33.825 --> 25:35.660
with no possibility of parole

25:35.702 --> 25:38.079
if only to make sure
restaurant hostesses everywhere

25:38.121 --> 25:39.873
get the message loud and clear.

25:44.169 --> 25:45.670
- I'm sorry.

25:47.922 --> 25:49.966
What can I do?
Tell me what I can do.

25:50.008 --> 25:52.761
I... I will do anything
you want, please.

25:52.802 --> 25:54.304
Please don't let them
take me to jail.

25:54.346 --> 25:56.139
Please. Please.

25:56.181 --> 25:57.849
[Cries]

25:57.891 --> 25:59.976
Please, please.

26:00.018 --> 26:02.395
What can I do?
You gotta tell me what I can do.

26:02.437 --> 26:04.939
You have to give me
a chance, please.

26:04.981 --> 26:06.858
I want you to listen to me,
please.

26:06.900 --> 26:08.818
I-I can do anything you want.

26:08.860 --> 26:11.321
I can-- I can--
I can do anything you want.

26:11.363 --> 26:13.782
I can live
with any terms you-you-you...

26:13.823 --> 26:15.700
Tell me what to do, please.

26:15.742 --> 26:18.244
I can bear anything
as long as it's not jail.

26:18.286 --> 26:21.915
[Sobbing]
Please. Please. I beg you.

26:21.956 --> 26:25.001
I beg you, please. Please.

26:25.043 --> 26:27.879
[Batty sobbing]
I beg you, please.

26:27.921 --> 26:30.090
- Stop crying.

26:30.131 --> 26:31.174
Right now.

26:31.216 --> 26:34.135
[Batty sobbing]

26:34.177 --> 26:35.178
Stop.

26:35.220 --> 26:40.058
[intense music]

26:56.116 --> 26:57.325
Clean my boots.

27:01.413 --> 27:02.789
- Of course.

27:08.169 --> 27:09.254
- With your tongue.

27:28.815 --> 27:32.152
[lips smacking against rubber]

27:45.999 --> 27:49.294
Everyone has
a sadistic streak.

27:49.336 --> 27:50.879
You learn that quick

27:50.920 --> 27:52.922
when you have someone
at your mercy.

27:52.964 --> 27:54.257
Malone: You little bitch.
[Slap]

27:54.299 --> 27:55.425
[Alba grunts]

27:55.467 --> 27:57.093
You had one job.

27:57.135 --> 27:58.428
- Easy, partner.

27:58.470 --> 28:00.930
- Or what? You understand
how this works, yes?

28:00.972 --> 28:02.140
The more witnesses we have,

28:02.182 --> 28:04.142
the more witnesses
we have to take care of.

28:04.184 --> 28:05.393
Congratulations.

28:05.435 --> 28:07.020
You just signed
her death sentence.

28:07.062 --> 28:08.897
- Why don't we discuss
this away from the children?

28:08.938 --> 28:10.815
- Hey! Hey!

28:12.233 --> 28:14.069
What's your name?

28:14.110 --> 28:15.111
- Inocencia.

28:15.153 --> 28:16.446
- Inocencia, quit cleaning shit

28:16.488 --> 28:18.990
and just go sit in the bathtub
with the others.

28:41.888 --> 28:44.307
- I always knew
it would end badly for you.

28:44.349 --> 28:47.060
- Sweet of you to say.

28:47.102 --> 28:49.312
- Who are you?

28:49.354 --> 28:51.147
- Nobody.

28:51.189 --> 28:53.108
- Everybody is somebody.

28:53.149 --> 28:56.444
- Not me.
I'm too hungover.

28:56.486 --> 28:58.071
Malone: Keep quiet in there!

29:02.200 --> 29:06.871
[***]
